subSubSection.paragraph:
This species is most similar to 
Ceresium promissum
Dillon & Dillon based on the key characters. It is distinguished from that species by having the mesosternal process basal notch angled (parallel-sided in 
Ceresium promissum
) and the pronotum having a narrow, glabrous, longitudinal line centrally located (restricted to posterior half in 
Ceresium promissum
). This species is endemic to Fiji and known only from Moala, Viti Levu, and Lau Islands. It has been collected from rotten logs and dead branches in August and October (
Dillon and Dillon 1952
).
